<item>
            <title>[SPARK-22577] executor page blacklist status should update with TaskSet level blacklisting</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22577</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;right now the executor blacklist status only updates with the BlacklistTracker after a task set has finished and propagated the blacklisting to the application level. We should change that to show at the taskset level as well. Without this it can be very confusing to the user why things aren&apos;t running.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13120044">SPARK-22577</key>
            <summary>executor page blacklist status should update with TaskSet level blacklisting</summary>
